Hi, Welcome to my Git & Github Repo. In this Repo I am going to let you know that How to download and Configure.
1.Download Git:
•	Go to the Git for Windows download page.
•	Click on this link https://git-scm.com/download/win
•	The download should start automatically. If not, click on the download link.
2.Run the Installer:
•	Locate the downloaded file (usually named Git-x.y.z-64-bit.exe) and double-click it.
•	Follow the installation wizard:
      1.	Select Destination Location: Choose where Git will be installed.
      2.	Select Components: You can typically keep the default components.
      3.	Choosing the default editor used by Git: You can select an editor (e.g., Vim, Nano, or Notepad++), or stick with the default (Vim).
      4.	Adjusting your PATH environment: Choose "Git from the command line and also from 3rd-party software" for default settings.
      5.	Choosing HTTPS transport backend: The default option "Use the OpenSSL library" is recommended.
      6.	Configuring the line ending conversions: Choose "Checkout Windows-style, commit Unix-style line endings" for default settings.
      7.	Configuring the terminal emulator to use with Git Bash: The default "Use MinTTY" is generally recommended.
      8.	Configuring extra options: You can typically leave the defaults.
•	Click Install and wait for the process to complete.
•	Click Finish to complete the installation.
